Source archiv Open-Baycom-Mailbox (OpenBCM)

-----------------------------------------------------------------------------
README in english language
-----------------------------------------------------------------------------
General notes:
- Have a look at config.h to switch on/off some features (default is
  an optimate selection, but perhaps you want to use/not use some other
  features).
- Read file "changes.txt" carefully, what has been changed
- After first start of a new version, check init.bcm for changed features

Hints for Linux user:
- you need GCC v4.x or higher, GCC <v4.x is NOT working
- look at makefile for some compiling options (dynamic or static).
- do a 'make' under linux to compile
- if you get some errors (warnings can be ignored) make sure
  that you have installed all compiler components
- to compile without Layer2 use:
  make -f makefile.nol2

Hints for Windows user:
- you need Microsoft Visual C++ 5.0 or 6.0 (english version!) for compiling
- you have to open workspace file bcm32.dsw and then compile with key F7

Hints for DOS user:
- you need Borland C++ DOS compiler
- you have to open project file bcm.prj and then compile with key F9
